Top Stories (January 2)

CALIFORNIA UTILITY OFFICIALS CONTINUE TO PRESS FOR HIGHER RATES
Utility officials continued pleas for massive rate hikes before a state 
commission Thursday and outlined plans for even more increases in 2001 if 
wholesale energy costs don't drop soon.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/01/krtbn/0000-0022-CC-UTILITY

UTILICORP SAYS ENDS MERGER WITH EMPIRE DISTRICT
Energy company UtiliCorp United Inc. said Tuesday it has terminated its 
$800-million merger agreement with Empire District Electric Co. due to 
regulatory uncertainties.
http://207.32.82.57/news/ElectricPower/01_02_2001.reutr-story-N02661441.html

GCC POWER GRID PROJECT TO BE REVIVED
The GCC power grid project, a dream project of the Gulf States mooted twenty 
years ago, is all set to be revived.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/industry
suppliers/2001/01/01/eng-industrysuppliers/eng-industrysuppliers_050753_8_7915
7518502325

ARKANSAS, OKLAHOMA, TEXAS STILL WITHOUT POWER; EAST DIGS OUT
As the lights slowly came back on in thousands of Arkansas homes, Gov. Mike 
Huckabee, who himself had lost power after the Christmas Day ice storm, urged 
residents to be patient.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/01/eng-djn/eng-djn_142041_33_6990885576233

